article.headline: Dartmouth 66, UC Davis 61
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Mike Lang made four 3-pointers and scored 16 points to lead Dartmouth to a 66-61 win over UC Davis Friday. Leon Pattman added 13 points and seven rebounds for Dartmouth (1-1), which got 12 points from Chuck Flynn and 10 from Michael Giovacchini. Vince Oliver scored 15 of his game-high 27 points for UC Davis (0-2) in the second half. Flynn tallied all 12 of his points during the first 10 minutes as Dartmouth jumped out to a 22-8 lead. UC Davis opened the second half with a 12-5 run to tie the score at 36-36 on a baseline drive by Rommel Marentez with 15:26 remaining. Marentez finished with 15 points. Dartmouth regained the lead on a Pattman 3-pointer that made it 39-36. After Dartmouth built the lead to 54-45, UC Davis made its final push, getting as close as 60-59 on an Oliver triple with 2:02 left. Dartmouth then put the game away from the foul line by making six of eight free throws down the stretch.
